### shrinkScalarLogicOp() {#a8f1944c0f1fec9c842ba7c07b84a96f2}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool SIShrinkInstructions::shrinkScalarLogicOp (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &amp; MI) const</>}>
Attempt to shrink AND/OR/XOR operations requiring non-inlineable literals.

For AND or OR, try using S&#95;BITSET&#123;0,1&#125; to clear or set bits. If the inverse of the immediate is legal, use ANDN2, ORN2 or XNOR (as a ^ b == ~(a ^ ~b)). 
<SectionUser title="Returns">
true if the caller should continue the machine function iterator
</SectionUser>
